scene.message:
Himeno: Father's going to{nl}
assign me a bodyguard this{nl}
time, so I won't be attacked{nl}
by demons.{waitkey}You should all get one too...{nl}
{wait_fr:48} ...Oh, but that's{nl}
impossible for you, isn't it.{nl}
Right, it costs money.{waitkey}So sorry.{waitkey}{ret}

She was supposed to be an{nl}
admirable girl working a job{nl}
for her family's sake, but...{color:0}{waitkey}{ret}

Himeno: Oh, Nanjo. Are you{nl}
still associating with{nl}
people like that?

Mark: "People like that"...?{wait_fr:32}{nl}
And just who d'you mean by{nl}
"people like that"...

Elly: ...{wait_fr:21}"People like{nl}
that"...?{wait_fr:32} Did I just hear{nl}
"people like that"...?{waitkey}I must have misheard,{nl}
surely?{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: True, these fools are{nl}
a hopeless lot, and may well{nl}
be "people like that"...{waitkey}{clearbox}...{wait_fr:21}Yet why does it anger me{nl}
to hear someone else say it?{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: What on earth...{wait_fr:32}{nl}
Himeno, did you eat something{nl}
that disagreed with you?{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: I always figure I{nl}
oughta choose my friends{nl}
more carefully too!{waitkey}Elly: Having too little{nl}
confidence is a problem,{nl}
but...{wait_fr:32} that was going a{nl}
